Indian Ocean
---
[5] Republic of Maldives
Date: Fri 8 Sep 2017 12:24
Source: Raajje.mv [edited]
https://raajje.mv/en/news/17350


Maldive Islands have received an award from WHO for eliminating measles. With Bhutan, the Maldives are the 1st 2 South East Asian nations to have eliminated the virus (Promed mail from Healthmap alerts)

The award was accepted by Minister of Health Abdulla Nazim Ibrahim.

In June [2017], the Maldives was commended by WHO for eliminating measles.

Maldives and Bhutan are the 1st 2 nations in the South-East Asian region to have eliminated measles.

The award for eradicating measles was conferred at WHO's 70th Regional Committee Session for the South-East Asian region.

[Byline: K. Male and Shan Anees ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It was reported by WHO on [Tue 13 Jun 2017] that Bhutan and the Maldives eliminated measles, becoming the 1st countries in their region to eliminate the highly infectious disease. The milestone was reached after no measles cases originating in the Maldives had been recorded since 2009 and none in Bhutan since 2012. Both countries launched immunisation programmes abound 40 years ago with mass vaccination. The WHO has set a 2020 deadline for the elimination of measles in the 11 countries it categorises as the Southeast Asia region. The region has averted an estimated 620 000 measles deaths in 2016 after carrying out vaccinations in the 11 countries, the WHO said.
Nearly 107 million children were reached with an additional dose of measles vaccine in the region between 2013 and 2016, according to the WHO.

Globally, measles remains a leading cause of death among young children in the developing world. The viral disease is spread through coughing and sneezing and can lead to pneumonia, brain inflammation or death.
Excerpted from https://www.reuters.com/article/health-measles/bhutan-and-maldives-eliminate-measles-who-idUSL8N1JA3AZ. - Mod.LK]

[A Healthmap/ProMED map of the Maldives can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5304434,143]
